{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3214353,"name":"Zane McElroy","username":"CoachZM","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/e480ec/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-06-15T03:28:32.518Z","cooked":"<p>I am working on programming our T-Shirt Cannon which has 6 tubes. I want to be able to press the A button and have it fire tube 1, then the next time I press it have it fire tube 2, then tube 3, etc… and once tube 6 is fired, then reset back to tube 1. I have tried the following code but when watching the lights on PCM they all flash and I can’t get it to advance from one to the next. I think the issue is that it is going through the code so quickly that it advances my variable while I am still pressing the button from the first one. I am using a timed robot and I have set the integer to 0 at the top of the code. Any suggestions would be greatly appreciated.</p>
