<p>Howdy! Really great job so far and im pretty sure you nailed the root issue! I think the code is looping so fast that even when you tap the A button, its going through all 6 states. The only fix you should need is to replace your <code>getAButton()</code> with <a href="https://github.wpilib.org/allwpilib/docs/release/java/edu/wpi/first/wpilibj/XboxController.html#getAButtonPressed()" rel="noopener nofollow ugc"><code>getAButtonPressed()</code></a> which only returns true once per button press. I would also recommend only calling it once and storing it in a variable. Really nice job! You got 95% of the way there!</p>
<p>Another note, try to use code blocks:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">//Launch Code
Boolean hasAButtonBeenPressed = controller.getAButtonPressed();
if(hasAButtonBeenPressed &amp;&amp; shotCount == 0) {
launchTube1.set(true);
shotCount ++;
}
else if (hasAButtonBeenPressed &amp;&amp; shotCount == 1) {
launchTube2.set(true);
shotCount++;
}
else if(hasAButtonBeenPressed &amp;&amp; shotCount == 2) {
launchTube3.set(true);
shotCount++;
}
else if(hasAButtonBeenPressed &amp;&amp; shotCount == 3) {
launchTube4.set(true);
shotCount++;
}
else if(hasAButtonBeenPressed &amp;&amp; shotCount == 4) {
launchTube5.set(true);
shotCount++;
}
else if(hasAButtonBeenPressed &amp;&amp; shotCount == 5) {
launchTube6.set(true);
shotCount = 0;
}
else{
launchTube1.set(false);
launchTube2.set(false);
launchTube3.set(false);
launchTube4.set(false);
launchTube5.set(false);
launchTube6.set(false);
}
</code></pre>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2023-06-15T03:42:15.454Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":140,"readers_count":139,"score":63.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":438191,"topic_slug":"using-same-button-for-multiple-solenoids-ifs-and-variables","display_username":"Owen Busler","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.wpilib.org/allwpilib/docs/release/java/edu/wpi/first/wpilibj/XboxController.html#getAButtonPressed()","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"XboxController (WPILib API 2023.4.3)","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":23320,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/using-same-button-for-multiple-solenoids-ifs-and-variables/438191/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3214356,"name":"Fritz G","username":"FritzG","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fritzg/{size}/175927_2.png","created_at":"2023-06-15T04:07:02.752Z","cooked":"<p>This is a really fun programming problem, and I couldn’t resist the urge to compact it a bit by putting all your solenoid objects into an array <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/slight_smile.png?v=12" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">Boolean hasAButtonBeenPressed = controller.getAButtonPressed();

DoubleSolenoid[] launchTubes = { 
    //Placeholder PCM Ids
    new DoubleSolenoid(0, 1),
    new DoubleSolenoid(2, 3),
    new DoubleSolenoid(4, 5),
    new DoubleSolenoid(6, 7),
    new DoubleSolenoid(8, 9),
    new DoubleSolenoid(10, 11)
};

if (hasAButtonBeenPressed) {
    launchTubes[shotCount].set(true);
    shotCount++;
    //thanks to @sanjithar for this suggestion, and SndMndBdy for an improvement on it
    shotCount %= launchTubes.length;
} else {
    for (DoubleSolenoid launchTube : launchTubes) {
        launchTube.set(false);
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p>Both ways will of course work, but especially as you run into more and more complex code, there’s a lot of value in minimizing the amount of code you need to look over when debugging.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2023-06-15T14:03:16.512Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":123,"readers_count":122,"score":109.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":438191,"topic_slug":"using-same-button-for-multiple-solenoids-ifs-and-variables","display_username":"Fritz G","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":5}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53275,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/using-same-button-for-multiple-solenoids-ifs-and-variables/438191/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":5}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":5,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3214358,"name":"Sanjith U","username":"sanjithar","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/sanjithar/{size}/193082_2.png","created_at":"2023-06-15T04:26:47.895Z","cooked":"<p>I would have done it the same way. Only thing is you’d probably want to reset <code>shotCount</code> to 0 when it exceeds the length of the array to avoid bounds errors and to have the repeated behavior the OP described.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2023-06-15T04:26:47.895Z","reply_cou